																		Enter the Savage Beasts!
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250578" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1455619569 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">16 Feb 2016 10:46</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2458018">
									

<p>MTF Eta-11 take to the stage in the 2016 MTF Contest! As well as being the lead performers in this piece, they will also be part of the ensemble for &quot;On Mount Golgotha&quot;, the ongoing canon relating to <a href="/scp-012">SCP-012</a>.</p>
<p>You don't need to have done any of the pre-reading about Junior Researcher Emma Stark's investigation of SCP-012, but in case you're interested, Emma was introduced in <a href="/the-journal-of-k-m-sandoval">The Journal of K M Sandoval</a>, and this tale follows immediately after <a href="/bigger-than-jesus">Bigger Than Jesus</a>.</p>
<p>Much thanks to the Site-19 String Quartet – <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2000367&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457339049" alt="WrongJohnSilver" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2000367)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/wrongjohnsilver" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2000367); return false;">WrongJohnSilver</a></span>, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cumaeansibyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(456737); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=456737&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457339049" alt="CumaeanSibyl" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=456737)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cumaeansibyl" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(456737); return false;">CumaeanSibyl</a></span> and <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=362048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1457339049" alt="Smapti" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=362048)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/smapti" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(362048); return false;">Smapti</a></span> – for their feedback and encouragement. Thanks also to MrWrong for review and comments on the forums.</p>
<p>This is the first of the MTF Eta-11 contest entries. If you are interested in reading on, below is a recommended reading order:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><a href="/a-convincing-lyre">A Convincing Lyre</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/an-impenitent-thief">An Impenitent Thief</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/project-proposal-2014-2112">Project Proposal 2014-2112: &quot;Dreams of Failure&quot;</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/scp-2402">SCP-2402</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/enjoy-the-silence">Enjoy the Silence</a></strong></li>
<li><strong><a href="/the-musical-suspects">The Musical Suspects</a></strong></li>
</ul>

