		<div class="post" id="post-2473092">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2473092)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2473092">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2156983&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250578" alt="psul" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2156983)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/psul" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2156983); return false;" >psul</a></span> <span class="odate time_1458058143 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">15 Mar 2016 16:09</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2473092">
									

<p>Thanks Kalinin - I'm pleased you liked it.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>This sets up a clear story, introduces to us to the main players in a manner that isn't just a straight info-dump&#8230;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>One of the interesting things about using the existing On Mount Golgotha canon was the fact that it made the introductory tale easier - Emma is a perfect audience surrogate, so having her meet Eta-11 allows a relatively natural entry for the characters (as opposed to introducing them through narration).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I like how carefully constructed this was in relation to other works; the cross-references all make sense, and represent a diversity of material from the wiki</p>
</blockquote>
<p>There are a few sets of cross references (the &quot;best tunes&quot; throwaway lines, the containment breach at the end) and they all came from simply searching through the &quot;acoustic&quot;, &quot;musical&quot; and &quot;auditory&quot; tags for anything that fit the bill. I really enjoyed that - it was a great way to find writing that I'd never come across otherwise, and I hope other teams found the same thing in their planning process. The containment breach, in particular, probably represents the entire set of skips that could plausibly escape under their own steam and require Eta-11's help to recapture.</p>

							</div>

								
					
